00163 ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
00164 /// Error and Status flags of the joint. 
00165 /// Bit 0: Overcurrent flag. This flag is set if overcurrent limit is exceeded. \n
00166 /// Bit 1: Undervoltage flag. This flag is set if supply voltage to low for motor operation. \n
00167 /// Bit 2: Overvoltage flag. This flag is set if the motor becomes switched off due to overvoltage. \n
00168 /// Bit 3: Overtemperature flag. This flag is set if overtemperature limit is exceeded. \n
00169 /// Bit 4: Motor halted flag. This flag is set if motor has been switched off. \n
00170 /// Bit 5: Hall error flag. This flag is set upon a hall error. \n
00171 /// Bit 6: Encoder error flag. This flag is set upon an encoder error. \n
00172 /// Bit 7: Winding error flag. [currently not used] \n
00173 /// Bit 8: Cycle time violation. [currently not used] \n
00174 /// Bit 9: Initialization error of sine commutation. This flag is set if initialization is failed. \n
00175 /// Bit 10: Position mode flag. This flag is set when the module is in positioning mode. \n
00176 /// Bit 11: Position end flag. This flag becomes set if the motor has been stopped at the end position. \n
00177 ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
00178 class ErrorAndStatus : public YouBotJointParameterReadOnly {
00179 friend class YouBotJoint;

00182
